components.name: Load and Modify Data
components.description: Ingests CSV files from the data directory, converts them to JSON format for downstream processing. Uses image default entrypoint/command.

connections.purpose: access raw CSV and JSON files

components.name: Data Reconciliation
components.description: Standardizes city names using the HERE geocoding service. Uses image default entrypoint/command.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful completion of Load and Modify Data

components.name: OpenMeteo Data Extension
components.description: Adds weather attributes from OpenMeteo to the dataset. Uses image default entrypoint/command.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful completion of Data Reconciliation

connections.purpose: Docker network for external API calls

components.name: Column Extension
components.description: Appends additional properties (e.g., id, name) to each record as defined by integration parameters. Uses image default entrypoint/command.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful completion of OpenMeteo Data Extension

components.name: Save Final Data
components.description: Consolidates the enriched dataset and exports it as a CSV file. Uses image default entrypoint/command.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful completion of Column Extension

connections.purpose: access JSON inputs and write CSV output

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

dataset_id.description: Identifier of the dataset to process

date_column_name.description: Name of the column containing date values

table_naming_convention.description: Pattern used to name output tables (e.g., 'JOT_{}')

primary_column.description: Column that holds the city name to be reconciled

optional_columns.description: Additional columns that may be used during reconciliation

reconciliator_id.description: Identifier of the reconciliator service to use

date_separator.description: Separator character used in date formatting for OpenMeteo requests

extender_id.description: Identifier of the column extender to apply

output_directory.description: Directory where the final enriched CSV file will be stored

DATA_DIR.description: Path to the shared data directory mounted into Docker containers

sources: Raw CSV files located in the shared data directory (/app/data) matching *.csv
sinks: Final enriched CSV file saved as enriched_data_{}.csv in the shared data directory
